---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Why Life Momentum Score measures net momentum instead of streaks — the philosophy behind tracking positive and negative habits and using delayed score reveals for honest self-improvement."
>
  <article class="container-page py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
        You're better at hiding from yourself than you think.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-body">
        You finished the week feeling productive. Three workouts, a couple of good books, early
        nights. So why does it feel like you didn't move an inch?
      </p>

      <div class="mt-16 space-y-16 sm:space-y-20">
        <!-- 1 · The comparison: streaks vs. a real ledger -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Streaks tell flattering lies</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Most habit apps only count the good stuff — then quietly look away from everything
            pulling the other way. Same week, two very different stories:
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <!-- Habit tracker view -->
            <div class="card p-5">
              <p class="eyebrow">Most habit trackers</p>
              <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5 font-mono text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Workout</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Reading</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Meditation</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-5 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
                <p class="text-xs text-mute">Result</p>
                <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-positive">“Great week.”</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Life Momentum view -->
            <div class="card p-5">
              <p class="eyebrow">Life Momentum</p>
              <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5 font-mono text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Workout</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Reading</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-positive">✓</span> Meditation</li>
              </ul>
              <ul class="mt-2.5 space-y-2.5 border-t border-hairline pt-2.5 font-mono text-sm">
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-negative">✗</span> Doomscrolling</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-negative">✗</span> Gambling</li>
                <li class="flex items-center gap-2.5 text-body"><span class="text-negative">✗</span> Poor sleep</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="mt-5 border-t border-hairline pt-4">
                <p class="text-xs text-mute">Result</p>
                <p class="mt-1 text-base font-medium text-ink">“Mixed week.”</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Life Momentum keeps one honest ledger.
            <span class="text-positive">Good habits add.</span>
            <span class="text-negative">Bad habits subtract.</span>
            The number you see is what's actually left over — so you can log five workouts, still
            land in the red, and finally understand why the week felt off.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2 · The reveal: stop grading by the hour -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Stop grading yourself by the hour</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Check a score every day and you start gaming it — chasing the number instead of living
            your life. So you can hide it.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-lg bg-hairline sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="bg-surface p-5">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">Score visible daily</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-mute">
                You optimize for the number. One bad morning feels like failure. You quit by Thursday.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-surface p-5">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">Score hidden until the period ends</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
                You log what really happened. No daily bias. You meet the result with fresh, honest eyes.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Weekly and Monthly modes lock the score away until the period ends.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="mt-6 border-l-2 border-hairline-strong pl-5 text-lg leading-relaxed italic text-ink">
            “Delayed score reveals help reduce daily bias and encourage more honest self-reflection.”
          </blockquote>
        </section>

        <!-- 3 · Privacy as a feature -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Yours, and only yours</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            This kind of honesty only works in private. So nothing about you ever leaves your device.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-4">
            <div class="card p-4 text-center">
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">No</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mute">account</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-4 text-center">
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">No</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mute">login</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-4 text-center">
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">No</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mute">server</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card p-4 text-center">
              <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-positive">100%</p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mute">on your device</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Everything lives in your browser. Close the tab, come back tomorrow, it's all still here.
            Just you and the truth.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-14 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary inline-flex">Start Tracking</a>
        <a href="/features" class="btn btn-secondary inline-flex">Explore features</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
